A chill wind blew in and a older barb from the back shouted, &quot;Lad, shut that door b'fore we en shut it on ye!&quot;.<br>
Pharius grinned.  He was born to the mountains, always alone, always on the outside.  He had known of Halas, but had never ventured there...seen that is.  Now he decided, was the time to make an appearence.  Things were getting sticky...the drow party hunted for him night and day aand would not give up.  3 drow had fell to his daggers already, their braided hair becoming a nice momento.  Pharius heard of a group which was very intolernt of outside races, with great pride, and a feirce eye for battle.  This was how a barbarian was supposed to be, no matter his calling.  Some did it toe to toe, some did it from the shadows, others behind a club or mace, but in esscence, all would know the feircocity of a true barbarian.<br>
<br>
No mercy to those who deserve none.<br>
<br>
Pharius walked over to a table where a old shaman sat, pressing his hand to his chest he spoke.<br>
&quot;I `ave come h're ta take a oath o' blood.  I wish ta join ye, The Shanks.&quot;<br>
<br>
and he stood and waited.<br>
<br>
